Adeline De Walt Reynolds https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adeline_De_Walt_Reynolds 0 Adeline De Walt Reynolds (September 19, 1862 – August 13, 1961) was an American character actress who made her film debut at the age of 79 playing the grandmother of James Stewart in Come Live with Me (1941). She continued to play in about 25 films and numerous television series until her death.
